''Entryphone is a registered trademark.''

An intercom system fitted at the entrance to a building, especially a block of flats, by which visitors can identify themselves to specific occupants before being admitted to the building.

The Entryphone Company Limited, holders of the Entryphone trade mark has been supplying and installing door entry systems since 1958.  

[http://www.entryphone.co.uk entryphone.co.uk]

This is not an advert.  As although Entryphone is the company which produces such equipment, the word "Entryphone" has become a generic term to describe telephone door entry systems; similar to Yale for rim locks and Hoover for vacuum cleaners.